&lt;p&gt;The&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Industrial Electrician&lt;/strong&gt; must possess fundamental and specialized knowledge and skills related to the installation and maintenance of electrical devices and components found in industrial settings. The Industrial Electrician inspects, installs, troubleshoots, repairs and services (includes calibration and preventive/predictive maintenance) electrical equipment such as motors, generators, pumps, heavy duty machines, environmental regulating systems, communication systems; and associated electrical and electronic controls for food production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Industrial Electrician is also responsible for working together with the rest of the maintenance team to complete Work Orders and follow a Preventive Maintenance Program.&amp;nbsp; This is a full-time role (40 hours per week), scheduled Monday - Friday, with the possibility of overtime based on business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
